# CODEOWNERS — Documentation Enforcement and Code Review
#
# This file defines ownership and review requirements for RIPP Protocol.
# It ensures that changes to critical paths are reviewed by domain experts
# and that documentation stays in sync with implementation.
#
# Reference: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Default ownership — all contributors can review general changes
* @Dylan-Natter

# Specification and Schema — require spec maintainer review
/SPEC.md @Dylan-Natter
/schema/** @Dylan-Natter

# Documentation — require docs owner review
/docs/** @Dylan-Natter
/README.md @Dylan-Natter
/CONTRIBUTING.md @Dylan-Natter

# CLI Tooling — require tool owner review
/tools/ripp-cli/** @Dylan-Natter

# VSCode Extension — require extension owner review
/tools/vscode-extension/** @Dylan-Natter

# GitHub Workflows — require workflow owner review
/.github/workflows/** @Dylan-Natter

# Examples and Templates — community can review, but maintainer approves
/examples/** @Dylan-Natter
/templates/** @Dylan-Natter

# Wiki Source — requires docs review (published automatically)
/docs/wiki/** @Dylan-Natter
